		<h3 class="subheader">WHAT IS HOMOEOPATHY?</h3>
		<div class="bodyContent">
			The entire system of Homeopathy is based upon the basic principle of “SimiliaSimilibusCurentur” which means, “Like Cures Like”. This further means that medicines which can produce certain effects on healthy individuals are capable of curing any illness which displays similar effects. This system of healing was founded by German Physician & Chemist. Dr. Samuel Hahnemann (1755 – 1843).<br /><br />
			Like other practitioners of his era, he also adopted the orthodox school of medicine to treat his patients. However within a short period of time he was dissatisfied with the unscientific & crude methods of the treatment, especially in cases where patients purged, sweated and bled. Soon Dr. Hahnemann gave up his mode of treatment to develop a rational method of healing.<br /><br />
			While translating Cullen’s MateriaMedica, he came across Cinchona, from which Quinine is derived and used for the treatment of Malaria. His eagerness to understand Quinine, made him try Cinchona on himself and to his surprise, he developed symptoms similar to Malaria.<br /><br />
			Amazed by his findings, Hahnemann experimented several other drugs and confirmed his observations. After 15 years of thorough observation & experimentation, he confirmed & concluded the law of “SimiliaSimilibusCurentur”.<br />
